---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../consts';
---

<Layout title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION}>
  <style>
    h1 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
      line-height: 1.3;
    }

    p {
      line-height: 1.75;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      color: #222;
    }

    .actions {
      margin-top: 2.5rem;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }

    .actions a {
      color: inherit;
      text-decoration: none;
      font-style: italic;
    }

    .actions a::before {
      content: '→ ';
      font-style: normal;
    }

    .actions a:hover {
      text-decoration: underline;
    }
  </style>

  <h1>Grappling is infinitely complex.</h1>

  <p>
    No document, no course, no system can capture it completely. That isn't a problem to solve
    — it's the starting point. Every serious grappler has to build their game around that
    reality, whether they acknowledge it or not.
  </p>

  <p>
    Fractal BJJ is an attempt to map high-level no-gi the way a practitioner actually thinks
    about it in real time. The full game is broken into 19 systems. Some are closed enough to
    document completely. Others are framework systems — too open to ever finish, where principles
    matter more than flowcharts. Treating these two types the same way is where most mental
    models break down.
  </p>

  <p>
    This site is how I organise the sport. It's a working document — built from training,
    teaching, competition, and the best available sources. Always in progress, never final.
  </p>

  <nav class="actions">
    <a href="/systems">Enter the system map</a>
    <a href="/approach">Read the full approach</a>
  </nav>
</Layout>
